import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['precipitation'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Precipitation')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['precipitation'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation (mm)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='temp_max', by='location', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('How does the maximum temperature vary across different locations?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Location')
    ax.set_ylabel('Maximum Temperature (Celsius)')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['wind'], data['precipitation'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Wind Speed (km/h)')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation (mm)')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind speed and precipitation?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Wind vs Precipitation'], loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    weather_counts = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    weather_counts_pivot = weather_counts.pivot_table(index='location', columns='weather', values='count').fillna(0)
    
    ax = weather_counts_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title('How does the weather condition vary across different locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend(title='Weather Conditions')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['temp_range'] = data['temp_max'] - data['temp_min']
    plt.hist(data['temp_range'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Temperature Range')
    plt.axvline(data['temp_range'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['temp_range'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Temperature Range (Celsius)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature range (temp_max - temp_min) across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
